nd gripping new photographs following Biehl and Eskerod's return to Vita. Anthropology at its finest, Vita is essential reading for anyone who is grappling with how to understand the conditions of life, thought, and ethics in the contemporary world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aInstitutional carezBrazilzPorto Alegre (Rio Grande do Sul) 0aInstitutional carezBrazilzPorto Alegre (Rio Grande do Sul). 0aMarginality, SocialzBrazilzPorto Alegre (Rio Grande do Sul) 0aMarginality, SocialzBrazilzPorto Alegre (Rio Grande do Sul). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951464423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520951464.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles